BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 77.75999999999999 600 Td (Chapter 2: Choosing Your Niche/Topic) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Your niche should be specific enough to attract a dedicated audience.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (A show about cooking is too broad. A show about one-pot meals is better.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Choose a topic you can talk about passionately for years, not months.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Research existing podcasts in your topic to find gaps you can fill.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (The best niches combine your expertise with audience demand.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Consider who your ideal listener is and what problems they have.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (True crime, business, comedy, health, and self-improvement are popular categories.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Niche down first, then expand once you build an audience.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Ask yourself: can I create fifty episodes on this topic without running out?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Your unique perspective and personality make you different from competitors.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Test your idea by listing twenty episode topics. If you struggle, pick another niche.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (The most successful podcasts solve a specific problem for a specific audience.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (2) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
