BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 39.360000000000014 600 Td (Chapter 4: Equipment You Need \(Budget Options\)) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (You can start with just your smartphone and a free recording app.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (For better quality, the Audio-Technica ATR2100x microphone costs about 70 dollars.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (The Samson Q2U is another excellent budget USB microphone around 60 dollars.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (USB microphones plug directly into your computer with no extra equipment.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (A pop filter for 10-15 dollars reduces harsh sounds on letters like P and B.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Use earbuds or headphones to monitor your audio while recording.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Record in a quiet room with soft surfaces like carpet, curtains, and pillows.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (A closet full of clothes makes an excellent free recording booth.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (You do not need expensive soundproofing panels when starting out.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (A simple microphone stand or boom arm keeps the mic at mouth level.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Total budget setup: under 100 dollars for professional-sounding audio.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Upgrade equipment only after you have consistently published for three months.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (4) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
