BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 81.6 600 Td (Chapter 5: Recording Software Setup) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Audacity is free, open-source recording software for Mac and Windows.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (GarageBand comes free on every Mac and is beginner-friendly for podcasting.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Download and install your chosen software before your first recording session.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Connect your USB microphone and select it as the input device in settings.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Set your recording format to WAV or AIFF for highest quality during recording.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Test your levels: speak at normal volume and aim for peaks around minus 6 dB.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Record a test segment and listen back to check for background noise.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Close other applications that might create notification sounds while recording.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Save your project file immediately so you do not lose work accidentally.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Create a folder structure to organize episode recordings by number and date.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (For remote interviews, Riverside.fm and Zencastr record each person separately.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Practice with your software before recording your actual first episode.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (5) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
