BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 120.0 600 Td (Chapter 7: Editing Basics) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Editing removes mistakes, long pauses, and filler words from your recording.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (In Audacity, use the selection tool to highlight sections you want to delete.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Remove obvious mistakes, ums, long silences, and off-topic tangents.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Do not over-edit. Some natural pauses and imperfections sound authentic.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Add your intro music at the beginning and outro music at the end.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Use royalty-free music from sites like Epidemic Sound or Free Music Archive.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Normalize your audio so the volume is consistent throughout the episode.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Apply noise reduction to remove background hum or fan noise.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Export your final file as MP3 at 128kbps which is standard for podcasts.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Name your file clearly: episode number, title, and date for easy organization.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Editing a thirty-minute episode typically takes sixty to ninety minutes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (As you improve at recording, editing time decreases significantly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (7) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
