BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 104.64 600 Td (Chapter 8: Creating Cover Art) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Your cover art is the first thing potential listeners see on podcast apps.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Apple requires artwork to be 3000 by 3000 pixels in JPG or PNG format.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Use bold, readable text that is visible even as a tiny thumbnail.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Choose contrasting colors that stand out among other podcast covers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Include your podcast name prominently and a brief tagline if space allows.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Avoid small text, busy backgrounds, or photos that are hard to see small.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Canva offers free podcast cover art templates that look professional.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Keep the design simple and clean. Less is more with small thumbnails.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Look at top podcasts in your category for design inspiration.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Your face or a relevant icon helps listeners recognize your show quickly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Hire a designer on Fiverr for 20-50 dollars if you want custom artwork.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (You can update your cover art later but a good first impression matters.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (8) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
