BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 100.80000000000001 600 Td (Chapter 11: Writing Show Notes) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Show notes are the text description that accompanies each episode.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (They help with discoverability since podcast apps search text, not audio.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Start with a compelling one to two sentence summary of the episode topic.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Include timestamps for key topics so listeners can jump to sections they want.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (List any resources, books, tools, or websites mentioned during the episode.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Add links to your social media and website for listeners who want more.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Include a call to action: subscribe, leave a review, or visit your website.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Use relevant keywords naturally in your show notes for search optimization.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Keep formatting simple since different apps display notes differently.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Write show notes before recording to serve as your episode outline.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Include guest bios and links when you have interview episodes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Good show notes take ten minutes to write and significantly boost discoverability.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (11) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
