BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 93.12 600 Td (Chapter 13: Monetization Options) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Sponsorships pay you to mention products or services during your episodes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (You typically need 1000-5000 downloads per episode to attract sponsors.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (CPM rates \(cost per thousand listeners\) range from 15-50 dollars for podcasts.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Affiliate marketing earns commission when listeners buy through your links.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Amazon Associates and other programs let you earn on product recommendations.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Sell your own products or services that align with your podcast topic.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Offer premium content through Patreon or Apple Podcast Subscriptions.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Coaching, consulting, or courses can be marketed through your podcast.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Listener donations through platforms like Buy Me a Coffee supplement income.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Merchandise like t-shirts and mugs works for podcasts with loyal fan bases.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Do not focus on monetization until you have a consistent audience first.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Multiple small revenue streams add up to significant podcast income over time.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (13) Tj ET

endstream
